Here's the full test smell audit for `OrderProcessorTests.cs`:

---

## Summary Dashboard

| Severity | Smell Count | Affected Tests |
|----------|-------------|----------------|
| 🔴 High  | 4           | 4              |
| 🟡 Medium | 4           | 4              |
| 🟢 Low   | 1           | 8 (class-wide) |
| **Total** | **9**       | **8 of 9 tests** |

---

## 🔴 High Severity

### 1. Conditional Test Logic — `ProcessOrder_SetsCorrectStatus` (line 31)

The `if/else` means only one branch ever runs per execution. One status value is **never verified**.

```csharp
// ❌ Current
if (result.TotalAmount > 100)
    Assert.AreEqual("PremiumProcessed", result.Status);
else
    Assert.AreEqual("StandardProcessed", result.Status);
```

**Fix:** Split into two tests with deterministic inputs:

```csharp
// ✅ Fixed
[TestMethod]
public void ProcessOrder_SmallOrder_SetsStandardStatus()
{
    var order = new Order { Items = { new OrderItem("SKU-CHEAP", 1) } };
    var result = new OrderProcessor(_db, _email, _inventory).ProcessOrder(order);
    Assert.AreEqual("StandardProcessed", result.Status);
}

[TestMethod]
public void ProcessOrder_LargeOrder_SetsPremiumStatus()
{
    var order = new Order { Items = { new OrderItem("SKU-EXPENSIVE", 10) } };
    var result = new OrderProcessor(_db, _email, _inventory).ProcessOrder(order);
    Assert.AreEqual("PremiumProcessed", result.Status);
}
```

### 2. Assertion-Free Test — `ProcessOrder_CompletesWithoutError` (line 43)

No assertion at all. This test passes even if `ProcessOrder` returns garbage — it only fails on an unhandled exception.

```csharp
// ❌ Current — passes no matter what
processor.ProcessOrder(order);
```

**Fix:** Assert on the expected outcome:

```csharp
// ✅ Fixed
var result = processor.ProcessOrder(order);
Assert.IsNotNull(result);
Assert.AreEqual("StandardProcessed", result.Status);
```

### 3. Sleepy Test — `ProcessOrder_AsyncNotification_IsSent` (line 98)

`Thread.Sleep(2000)` makes this test slow and non-deterministic. On a loaded CI machine, 2 seconds may not be enough; on a fast machine it wastes time.

```csharp
// ❌ Current
processor.ProcessOrderAsync(order);
Thread.Sleep(2000);
Assert.IsTrue(_email.WasNotificationSent(order.Id));
```

**Fix:** Await the async operation, or use a polling helper with a timeout:

```csharp
// ✅ Fixed
await processor.ProcessOrderAsync(order);
Assert.IsTrue(_email.WasNotificationSent(order.Id));
```

### 4. Mystery Guest — `ImportOrders_FromCsv_ParsesCorrectly` (line 144)

Hard-coded path `C:\TestData\orders.csv` couples the test to a specific machine's file system. This will fail in CI and on any other developer's machine.

```csharp
// ❌ Current
var orders = processor.ImportOrders(
    File.ReadAllText(@"C:\TestData\orders.csv"));
```

**Fix:** Inline the test data or use an embedded resource:

